The paper deals with land-use classification using deep neural networks and remote sensing images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves using pseudo-labeling and sample selection, which is a common technique in semi-supervised learning (cs.AI). The paper also involves image segmentation, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
